# env.d — drop-in shell snippets sourced by init.rc.
#
# Each *.env file here is sourced (in alphabetical order) on shell startup.
# Use plain shell syntax, e.g.:
#
#   export FOO=bar
#   export PATH=$HOME/extra/bin:$PATH
#
# Naming:
#   *.env         committed to the repo, synced across machines (generic config)
#   *.local.env   git-ignored, for machine-specific or secret values
#
# Order with numeric prefixes if it matters: 00-paths.env, 50-tools.env, ...
# This file itself (no .env suffix) is NOT sourced; it only documents the format.
